  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2009-11-06",
    "date": "2010-02-22T21:49:40Z",
    "text": "Military Spouse Pin Act - Requires the design of a spouse-of-a-combat-veteran lapel button to identify and recognize the spouse of a member of the Armed Forces who is serving in a combat zone for a period of more than 30 days.\n\nDirects the: (1) Secretary of the military department concerned to present the button to such a spouse; and (2) Secretary of Defense (DOD) to make the button available to qualifying spouses of veterans of military conflicts that took place before the enactment of this Act."
  },
